We now retry updates for auto scaling groups when evaluating scaling policies. The existing configuration is used to control the retry count:

{code}
# euca-describe-properties bootstrap.tx.concurrent_update_retries
PROPERTY	bootstrap.tx.concurrent_update_retries	10	
{code}

if there are many clients executing scaling policies for the same auto scaling group then it may be necessary to update the configuration accordingly.

I tried several times updating the asg concurrently and did not see this issue. 
{noformat}
for i in {1..100}; do euscale-update-auto-scaling-group --desired-capacity $(($i%2+1)) elbscale & done;
{noformat}
